<TEXT>
sen dave durenberger received a warm 
welcome home from republicans meeting at a state convention friday 
he vowed to survive an ethics investigation into his financial 
dealings 
ive got the best friends in all the world durenberger told 
a luncheon of the independent republicans the state party it was 
his first public appearance since the senate ethics committee on 
wednesday completed two days of hearings 
durenberger received a standing ovation from the 1300 luncheon 
guests when he entered the banquet room and another when he 
finished his 20minute speech delegates gathered around the 
12year senate veteran and handshakes hugs and kisses were 
exchanged 
im learning so many lessons these days about how tough times 
bring out the best in you and the best in your friends 
durenberger said 
durengerger said he would not resign 
i just stand on the election results of november 1988 he 
said this is a sixyear term 
the ethics committee met for two days to investigate allegations 
that durenberger tried to cirumvent senate limits on speaking fees 
and tried to hide his ownership in a minneapolis condominium to 
collect travel reinbursements 
durenberger did not refer specifically to the allegations but 
apologized 
ive made mistakes and im taking responsibility for every 
single one of them he said adding that he acted in good faith 
and did not violate the public trust 
durenberger focused his speech on the accomplishments of the 
reagan and bush administrations and on his work ahead in the 
senate durenberger noted that he had been selected as one of seven 
senate conferees to work out differences with the house on the 
clean air act 
