a snow surfer who made pioneering 
descents in the himalayas and the alps was killed while trying to 
conquer a steep slope on mont blanc police said 
bruno gouvy 27 skidded on an ice patch shortly after being 
dropped by helicopter friday on the top of the green needle a 
13523foot peak on mont blanc in the french alps police said 
as those aboard the helicopter including a film crew looked 
on gouvy skidded more than 3000 feet down a steep face before 
falling into a crevasse 
snow surfing an increasingly popular sport is a form of skiing 
on a single board positioned like a surfer ski poles are not used 
gouvy reportedly held the altitude record for his sport with a 
1989 descent on mount everest starting at 27650 feet 
gouvy who last year snowsurfed down the west face of the eiger 
in the swiss alps also was an experienced mountain climber and a 
devotee of freefall parachuting 
