<TEXT>
an archaeological team is sifting through 
a sierra nevada campsite for remnants from the final days of george 
and jacob donner whose dreams of life in sunny california ended 
near here in icy disaster 
the two brothers from illinois and most of their party died 144 
years ago when a raging october snowstorm halted their westward 
trek and sealed their fate 
donald hardesty an archaeologist at the university of nevada 
reno is leading a team of students and volunteers in an effort to 
pinpoint the exact whereabouts of the brothers last camp at alder 
creek 
this camp is not nearly as well known or understood through 
written accounts he said thursday 
the donner families stopped at alder creek when a wagon axle 
broke the rest of the party continued to a lake about five miles 
away now known as donner lake 
incessant snow trapped both groups for six months in 18461847 
as starvation set in they ate boiled hides for nourishment when 
those were gone they turned to the flesh of their comrades who 
died of weakness 
of the 87 people who became stranded 39 survived nine of the 
12 adults and nine children with the donner families lived to see 
the spring the donner brothers did not 
hardesty said it is believed george donner used tree limbs 
propped against a giant ponderosa pine that still towers over the 
site and covered them with animal hides and quilts for a shelter 
jacob donner created a similar leanto for his family about 200 
yards away 
hardesty hopes to uncover the location of a third camp believed 
to have been used by teamsters traveling with the families 
armed with buckets brushes trowels and sifters 19 students 
and 10 volunteers sifted the soil near the two sites on thursday in 
the joint venture of the university and the us forest service 
as the excavating team worked in the warm june sunshine yellow 
and purple wildflowers bloomed in a nearby meadow and the sweet 
scent of sagebrush perfumed the air but almost as a reminder of 
the task gray clouds hugged the snowcapped peaks of the sierra 
hardesty said the group hopes to find small items and fragments 
at alder creek 
he said diaries were kept by those at the donner lake cabins 
but no writings have been found near the alder creek site 
hardesty participated in a 1984 excavation of the donner lake 
site where bone fragments cloth remnants chips of pottery and 
hardware were uncovered the most significant find there he said 
was a bronze roman catholic medallion 
</TEXT>
