<TEXT>
sveta and oleg have signed up to marry but they 
wont be around to hear the wedding bells theyll be too busy 
shopping 
in an illustration of how desperate soviets are for food and 
consumer goods sveta and oleg have applied to marry just to get 
the right to shop in a special store for brides and grooms 
when they applied wedded bliss was the furthest thing from 
their minds although the couple is in love and living together 
olegs thoughts were on an imported mans suit cuff links gold or 
silver wedding rings and imported shoes svetas were on her own 
ring imported shoes pantyhose and mascara 
for both it was a chance to shop in gemini part of a 
nationwide chain of stores that is an oasis in a desert of deficits 
here is how the scam works a single or divorced soviet finds a 
partner and applies to marry at a government registration office 
they pay a 15ruble 24 fee the couple is assigned a date for an 
official ceremony and is given a prized booklet of coupons for the 
gemini store as well as food shops meant to supply wedding parties 
the couple can shop at the stores until the wedding day when 
the coupons expire they dont show up for the official wedding 
and their marriage application is automatically voided 
then they can start all over again and if their faces become 
too familiar at the registration office they can just go to 
another 
thats why sveta and oleg have no intention of getting married 
the scam is so lucrative that sveta has applied to marry three 
times since november once with oleg twice with his friends 
thousands are participating onethird of all soviets applying 
to marry do so only so they can shop in the special stores state 
televisions breakfast show 120 minutes reported in april 
and that does not include other matches that are made merely so 
one partner can obtain a residence permit in a city where the other 
lives 
looking for loopholes even in such a sacred institution as 
marriage has become a survival technique in a system that has 
failed to offer soviets the food and consumer goods they want 
its the situation in this state which leads people to such 
things where you cant spend money on anything except lowquality 
food said viktor a 31yearold muscovite like oleg viktor 
applied to marry a friend of his girlfriend in may so they could 
obtain access to the special store 
theres such a terrible deficit you cant buy anything in the 
regular stores said sveta a 28yearold eye doctor she 
declined to give her surname fearing its publication would help 
authorities track her down 
the fear was largely unfounded because what she and the 
thousands of other soviets are doing is not illegal 
its a moral not a legal issue said valentina borzhenkova 
director of moscows wedding palace no 1 where weddings are 
performed its everyones right if all formalities are 
followed 
if all the offices had computers this couldnt happen 
because they could check whether you have applied at more than 
one sveta said but computers are as rare as efficient 
bureaucrats in the soviet government so couples can apply as often 
as they like 
the bureaucrats admit they are powerless to end the practice 
it will stop only when there are no deficits in the country 
mrs borzhenkova said 
at the gemini store sveta has bought american shoes virtually 
unavailable elsewhere in the soviet union and gold rings she 
travels to a nearby socialist country and and resells the rings 
at a hefty profit other goods also have a handsome return 
imported womens shoes bought at gemini for 55 rubles 89 can be 
peddled on the black market for 150 rubles 243 she said 
the special stores however are not a completely reliable 
source perhaps because of the high number of fictitious marriages 
even the special stores have sporadic supplies and long lines 
sometimes a six hourwait 
if you want everything you must go every day and still 
theres no guarantee youll get everything you want sveta said 
one day this month gemini where only customers holding a 
coupon booklet are admitted was selling 400ruble 648 gold 
rings and 55ruble 89 womens shoes from yugoslavia and hungary 
aside from its treasure trove of goods the store is set apart 
in other ways it is well lit clean and colorful with decorations 
in a celestial theme 
but there is an even better shop nearby for couples celebrating 
their 25th and 50th anniversaries sveta would love to get into 
that one but admits with a laugh unfortunately grandmothers 
and grandfathers wont run back and forth to the registration 
offices 
