<TEXT>
the blaze aboard the leaking mega borg 
has been extinguished and firefighters doused the sizzling 
supertanker today to avoid a flareup 
the fire was put out friday but coast guard and state officials 
warned that the norwegian ship crippled in an explosion june 8 
still posed a threat 
there are no flames however its still real hot and if we 
walk away from it right now it may reflash its not yet dead 
coast guard chief petty officer todd nelson said 
the accident left 43 million gallons of light african crude in 
the gulf of mexico the fifth worst spill in us history tar 
balls from a 10mile long slick were expected sunday on the bolivar 
peninsula about 40 miles east of galveston 
tar balls from the spill had been expected to hit shore friday 
but jerry galt of the national oceanic and atmospheric 
administration in houston said changing currents and atmospheric 
conditions delayed their arrival 
scientists on friday unleashed experimental oileating bacteria 
on a patch of the slick and awaited results of the procedure 
called bioremediation 
salvage crews today hoped to transfer oil remaining in a 
ruptured 55 million tank to an undamaged tank to stop a continuing 
leak and to balance the 886foot ship the supertanker was loaded 
with 38 million gallons of oil 
an official from det norske veritas norways equivalent to the 
american bureau of shipping was expected to board the mega borg to 
inspect damage over the weekend 
the ship with its rear section awash and seared by fiery 
explosions was clear of smoke for the first time friday 
i feel like i am face to face with my enemy said texas 
water commission chairman bj buck wynne looking at the 
listing hulk from a coast guard boat about 100 yards away 
for the first time since this thing began im beginning to 
believe we can beat it but i know there is going to be a next 
time wynne said 
more than two dozen boats were expected to continue skimming 
spilled oil today salvage crews said they have collected 146389 
gallons of oil the coast guard said friday most of the light crude 
that spilled either evaporated or burned and less than 22000 
gallons remained in the water 
carl oppenheimer a scientist who developed bioremediation and 
was eager to see it tested for the first time on oil in open seas 
joined officials unleashing trillions of oileating microbes on the 
rustcolored slick 
they sprayed the bacteria mixture on an acre of oil about three 
miles southeast of the mega borg 
the bacteria will break the oil down into harmless fatty acids 
that will be consumed by marine life said oppenheimer a 
university of texas microbiologist who has been working on the 
process for 15 years 
oppenheimer predicted the acre would be clear of oil in one or 
two days 
this is breakthrough technology texas land commissioner 
garry mauro said 
investigators have not determined the cause of the fire that 
killed two of the ships 41 crew members injured 17 and left two 
missing and presumed dead 
a panel convened by norwegian consul general erik leikvang 
concluded a threeday hearing friday 
at the hearing officials asked third mate jaipal singh mahlawat 
to elaborate on a fuel leak discovered in the ships pump room six 
hours before the explosion 
i saw the pump man he was screwing a coupling back to stop 
the oil from leaking mahlawat said no oil was leaking he had 
already wiped it out 
the pump man putham mahamood testified thursday through a 
translator that he performed no measurable repair work the day 
of the explosion 
the mega borgs chief engineer told the panel thursday one of 
the vessels pumps was leaking fuel about six hours before the 
explosion and a norwegian shipping inspector said some other pumps 
were overdue for an inspection 
coast guard investigator ruben arredondo who sat in on 
testimony but was not a member of the panel said the oil leak may 
have provided the fuel source for a fire sparked by something such 
as a bad light fixture 
the panel will send its report to the norwegian maritime 
investigative bureau which will determine if the ship is seaworthy 
and if there is any criminal liability 
</TEXT>
