<TEXT>
here are the key facts about bioremediation an experimental 
plan to dump oileating bacteria on the mega borg oil slick in the 
gulf of mexico off galveston texas 
description bioremediation uses naturally occurring bacteria 
microbes which have a sandlike consistency to reduce oil to an 
emulsion of fatty acids the emulsion sinks and is consumed by 
marine life microbes die when they cannot find any more oil to eat 
uses the microbes have been used for years to clean up 
hazardous waste sites treat sewage and wastewaters and extract 
oil from tight geologic formations they were used to clean some 
rocks on shore after the exxon valdez accident last year in alaska 
their use off texas was the first time bioremediation has been used 
in the water to clean up an oil spill 
plan state officials mixed the bacteria in 100gallon tanks of 
salt water and shot it through hoses from a coast guard cutter 
amount officials planned to use 100 pounds of the bacteria each 
day for three to four days on freshly spilled oil near the vessel 
cost the test will cost the state about 50000 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

