actorauthor peter ustinov and writer kingsley 
amis became the newest knights of the realm today in the birthday 
honors list of queen elizabeth ii 
ustinov the 69yearold actor author dramatist film 
director newspaper columnist and raconteur was named a knight 
bachelor so was amis 67 author of the old devils lucky 
jim and most recently the folks that live on the hill 
ustinov who was made a cbe or companion of british empire in 
1975 was asked how he felt about being knighted 
i cannot see it making any difference i shall go on working 
its like another flag on everest ustinov said 
my reaction is one of unqualified delight amis said it 
is wonderful news 
the honors and others to writer anita brookner historian 
martin gilbert and fashion designer bruce oldfield were actually 
chosen by the government of prime minister margaret thatcher 
the government rewards the loyalty and service of hundreds of 
people twice each year at the new year and in june in honor of 
the monarchs official birthday 
queen elizabeth was born april 21 1926 but her official 
birthday is marked on a day in june when there is a marginally 
better chance of sunny weather for parades and celebrations 
the honors list showered medals and awards on hundreds of other 
britons some of whom made their mark in obscure professions 
the most rev robert runcie receives a peerage that will enable 
him to sit in the house of lords as baron runcie following his 
retirement as anglican archbishop of canterbury next year 
dame lydia dunn a senior hong kong legislator who has become a 
wellknown figure in the preparations for chinas takeover of the 
british colony in 1997 becomes a baroness 
ms brookner who won the prestigious booker prize in 1984 for 
her novel hotel du lac was made a cbe the same honor went to 
actress eileen atkins an actress and cocreator of the television 
series upstairs downstairs 
oldfield 39 reared in a yorkshire childrens home became a 
favorite fashion designer of the princess of wales he was made an 
obe or officer of the order of british empire 
tracy edwards 27 whose allwoman crew placed second in their 
class in the whitbread aroundtheword yacht race became an mbe 
or member of the order of british empire 
tucked away in the shadow of these luminaries among the head 
librarians tax inspectors and civil service secretaries are 
professions less glamorous than drama and fashion 
british empire medals went to herbert plenty cheesegrader for 
the milk marketing board and florence clary the keykeeper of 
mistley towers essex 
the honors bear nothing except a medal and the right to put 
letters such as obe and mbe after a name but they are a matter of 
great pride to recipients 
