force there 
xu said there are no plans for further talks the hanoi 
discussions were the fourth round of sinovietnamese talks over the 
past year and a half 
vietnam has sought to improve ties with china as the soviet 
union cuts back its economic and political support for hanoi and 
eastern european countries drift toward the west 
official radio hanoi on thursday gave only a brief and vague 
report on the talks indicating little progress was made 
the latest efforts to end the fighting in cambodia were set back 
earlier this month when the khmer rouge the strongest guerrilla 
faction refused to sign a ceasefire pact in tokyo saying it was 
denied equal representation in the negotiations china also refused 
to support the agreement 
