whipped cream squirt guns and balloons may 
not seem like conventional weapons in the war against drugs but 
they are an important part of a new hampshire psychologists 
arsenal 
lee wotherspoon approaches the battle against addiction with his 
own army a group called dad or drugs are dangerous 
the organizations mission is to show young people how to have 
fun without drugs and to encourage fathers to get involved in 
their childrens lives 
wotherspoon cofounded dad with ed ahlman of kingston whose son 
chris committed suicide in 1988 wotherspoon had counseled chris 
who was addicted to drugs before his death 
we got together to decide what we could do about the problems 
facing kids especially drugs ahlman said adding that the group 
currently has hundreds of members in new england 
the deficit is for fathers women are out there wanting to do 
whatever they can to help their kids and feeling torn when theyre 
struggling between work and family and children wotherspoon 
said the fathers forget they need to have it pulled together 
for them 
dad sponsors among other things natural high parties 
which feature activities such as squirt gun fights whipped cream 
battles balloon volleyball and limbo contests in the mud fathers 
