the kgb has long been thought to be one of the organizations 
that brought gorbachev to power five years ago 
the kgb or committee on state security once terrorized soviet 
citizens and harassed foreigners it has said it is reorienting 
itself toward the struggle against organized crime and drug 
trafficking in cooperation with other foreign intelligence agencies 
foreign residents of moscow notice much less surveillance than 
in the past 
kalugin revealed no secrets during his appearance and did not 
discuss specific kgb cases but he said he still feared 
repercussions 
for the time being it is only publicity that can curb the 
kgb he told reporters 
the supreme soviet legislature formally oversees the agency but 
has done nothing to rein it in he said 
kalugin said kgb agents are still spreading disinformation about 
leaders of the political reform movement still tapping telephones 
still playing dirty tricks 
kalugin said legitimate domestic kgb operations should be placed 
under the interior ministry which is responsible for uniformed 
police intelligence services should be placed directly under the 
president and kgb border guards should be transferred to control 
of the customs service he said 
boris n yeltsin the radical reformer and new president of the 
russian federation has made a similar proposal to merge the kgb 
into a single investigations agency 
kalugin who speaks english well said he worked from 19581970 
as a kgb agent in the united states first as a radio moscow 
correspondent and then as a first secretary in the soviet embassy 
in washington 
he said he was certain during his tour in the united states that 
the cia had identified him as a spy but no action was taken 
against him 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

