meana of the european community said 
he spoke after ministers from seven eastern european nations 
reported on pollution in their countries at a oneday meeting in 
dublin with ministers of the european community 
the ministers from 19 nations planned an attack on industrial 
contamination of the air water and land that has built up over 
decades 
they signed a communique setting out ideas to tackle nuclear and 
toxic waste acid rain and water pollution in the emerging 
democracies of eastern europe 
it stressed that protection of the environment was one of the 
most urgent political priorities 
the agreement commits poland the soviet union hungary 
yugoslavia east germany czechoslovakia bulgaria and the european 
community members to look at ways of effective pollution monitoring 
and curbing harmful practices that poison the environment 
the nations also called for the establishment of a new european 
