<TEXT>
honda motor co ltd will sell chrysler corp 
jeeps through some of its dealers in japan beginning this fall the 
companies said friday 
in a joint announcement honda and chrysler said 1991model jeep 
wranglers and cherokee sportutility vehicles will be sold in about 
750 of hondas primo dealerships the companies said they expect 
about 2000 jeeps would be sold in the next model year 
that would more than double chryslers sales in japan and marks 
the first time a us company has used hondas japanese dealers to 
sell vehicles 
chrysler chairman lee iacocca for years has complained about 
being shut out of the japanese market either because of 
governmental regulations or dealer resistance 
last year chrysler sold about 1500 jeeps and cars through 
chrysler japan sales ltd a joint venture between the us company 
and j osawa amp co of japan 
japanese dealers rarely handle more than one car make at a 
dealership there is an incredible amount of dealer loyalty to 
their companies in japan auto analyst mary anne sudol of fitch 
investors services inc said friday 
she called the hondachrysler deal a nice little breakthrough 
for chrysler 
under the agreement about half of hondas primo dealer network 
a collection of 1755 businesses that market family oriented cars 
will distribute cherokee and wrangler vehicles 
honda said in a statement released in japan that the cherokee 
would sell for about 33300 and the wrangler for about 23800 
base prices for 1990 versions of the vehicles are 15545 for the 
cherokee and 11599 for the wrangler 
honda sells its own sporty cars through its verno dealerships 
and luxury cars through its clio dealerships in all honda has 
about 2500 dealerships in japan 
general motors corp the no 1 automaker in the us sells 
vehicles in japan through suzuki motor co dealers 
ford motor co the nations second largest automaker uses a 
290dealership autorama network to sell ford and mazda vehicles 
under ford nameplates in japan ford expects to sell about 100000 
cars and light trucks through autorama including a mini 
sportutility vehicle this year 
